data.title: What awards has William Butler Yeats won?
data.meta_description: He won the 1923 Nobel prize for Literature.
data.text:
What did William Butler Yates write?

What awards have Romeo and Juliet won?

Since Romeo and Juliet are just characters in a story, they only won whatever awards the story says they won. And according to the story they each won the golden statue award. Posthumously. Did Shakespeare's play win any awards? Nope. They didn't have awards for literature back then. Not even poet laureates.

What Famous Poet from Ireland won the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1923?

William Butler Yeats, a famous poet from Ireland, won the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1923. Yeats is known for his contributions to Irish literature and his works that have had a lasting impact on the literary world.

How many Irish writers won the Pulitzer prize?

As of 2009, there are only four: William Butler Yeats (1923), George Bernard Shaw (1925), Samuel Beckett (1969) and Seamus Heaney (1995). The official Nobel Prize web site lists Shaw as a UK citizen although he was born and raised in Dublin.
